<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2919] OutOfMemory exception possible when using ByteMessage-s due to JVM bug</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2919</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to following  &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=4797189&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=4797189&lt;/a&gt; the custom deflator is not closed when used with DeflaterOutputStream. A workaround is to explicitly close it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12483806">AMQ-2919</key>
            <summary>OutOfMemory exception possible when using ByteMessage-s due to JVM bug</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
